Seven persons are reportedly injured in Rafiki and Dutse Kura communities of Bassa Local Government Area of Plateau State after a fresh attack by suspected Fulani herdsmen on Wednesday.

The president of Miango Youths Development Association, Lawrence Zongo, stated this in a  message to correspondents on Wednesday that: “There was a fresh attack this morning around 6:30am.

“More than seven people have been seriously injured by Fulani terrorists. One person is missing.

“We appreciate the efforts of management of Enos Hospital and Bingham University Teaching Hospital in Jos for taking time in treating the injured ones.”